Sentencas: Protective Cu-Ni-Mn-O spinel coatings on UNS430 solid oxide fuel cells interconnects were formed by oxidizing electroplated nickel, copper, and manganese in air at 800 degrees C. Nickel prevented delamination and buckling damage of the coatings.
Titulo: Nickel substituted CuMn2O4 spinel coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Substituting copper with nickel up to 40% in CuMn2O4 spinel decreased conductivity slightly from similar to 110 to similar to 95 S/cm at 800 degrees C. XRD showed Cu0.77Ni0.45Mn1.78O4 exhibited predominantly spinel phase
Titulo: Nickel substituted CuMn2O4 spinel coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: whereas nickel free Cu1.18Mn1.82O4 exhibited mixed oxide phase.
Titulo: Nickel substituted CuMn2O4 spinel coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Nickel promotes adhesion and formation of uniform protective coatings as <1 mu m Cr-oxide scale formed after 120 h of oxidation and it also stabilizes the spinel phase at lower temperatures.
Titulo: Nickel substituted CuMn2O4 spinel coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnects
